1
00:00:10,433 --> 00:00:12,300
<i>Why? Do you think I don't know
what you're doing?</i>

2
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:14,700
<i>You're using me to make
the doctor jealous, right?</i>

3
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:16,167
<i> Let me explain.</i>

4
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,733
<i>- No need.
- It's up to you</i>

5
00:00:17,867 --> 00:00:19,667
<i> whether you believe me or not!</i>

6
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,267
<i>But the killer killed
another gay man!</i>

7
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,400
<i> Tootsie!</i>

8
00:00:23,533 --> 00:00:25,300
<i>Don't bother him anymore,
he's probably resting.</i>

9
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:27,033
<i>- Hey, Friend!
- Tootsie!</i>

10
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:29,533
<i> Hello, Tonyo?</i>

11
00:00:29,667 --> 00:00:30,900
<i> Come to the dressing room now!</i>

12
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:32,400
<i> There's a performer dead!</i>

13
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:34,533
<i>And he has a birthmark
on his hand!</i>

14
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:37,067
<i>I just can't remember
what he looks like.</i>

15
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,000
<i>I heard someone
was killed inside.</i>

16
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,200
<i> Really?</i>

17
00:00:40,333 --> 00:00:41,333
<i>What's that? When you entered
the dressing room,</i>

18
00:00:41,467 --> 00:00:42,800
<i>- Tootsie was dead?
- Yes, Chief.</i>

19
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,200
<i>I already talked
to the bouncer, Chief.</i>

20
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:45,967
<i> Don't let anyone out.</i>

21
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:47,967
<i>Maybe the killer is just there
with the customers.</i>

22
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:49,900
<i>But you act as if
she's your girlfriend.</i>

23
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:51,000
<i> Dude, stop it.</i>

24
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:53,300
<i> Bro, you're not her type.</i>

25
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:55,267
<i>That's enough! Vince!
That's enough!</i>

26
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:57,200
<i>Enriquez, your father just died.</i>

27
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:58,967
<i>You can go home now.
That's not a request.</i>

28
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,367
<i> Go talk to Chief.</i>

29
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:03,133
<i>Aren't you on leave now
because your father died?</i>

30
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:05,433
<i>Do you really not want
to believe that I'm okay?</i>

31
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:06,533
<i> Okay, I'll talk to Chief.</i>

32
00:01:06,667 --> 00:01:08,533
<i>No, never mind.
I'm going home!</i>

33
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:12,367
- Stop them!
- Let go of me!

34
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:13,333
I will not let go of you!

35
00:01:13,467 --> 00:01:14,567
Hey! What's that?

36
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:15,700
What are you doing?

37
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:16,867
Oh, nothing, Faye.

38
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,300
Just ask Vince.

39
00:01:19,533 --> 00:01:21,467
What were you two
fighting about?

40
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:22,800
Stop it!

41
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:24,633
Let me go!
Dude, let me go!

42
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:26,733
I'll only let you go
if you stop.

43
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:27,533
What? Will you stop?

44
00:01:27,667 --> 00:01:29,200
Yes, yes.

45
00:01:29,333 --> 00:01:30,267
You're sure?

46
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,800
Yes, yes!

47
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,333
Be thankful Faye is here.

48
00:01:38,467 --> 00:01:40,067
I'm leaving.

49
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,033
Vince, wait a minute.

50
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:48,300
Faye...

51
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,867
Looks like you need
to tell him the truth.

52
00:01:58,967 --> 00:02:00,333
Vince...

53
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:04,467
I committed a sin against you.

54
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:39,500
Sir Eric, thank you.

55
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:40,900
Yes, Sir Eric.

56
00:02:41,033 --> 00:02:42,767
We really enjoyed
ourselves today.

57
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:45,733
You didn't inform us
that you're a good hitter.

58
00:02:45,867 --> 00:02:47,067
Oh...

59
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:50,067
- That's right.
- And hopefully next time again.

60
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:51,633
We'll go ahead, Sir Eric.

61
00:02:51,767 --> 00:02:52,900
- Oh, okay.
- Let's go, Selena!

62
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:54,500
Let's go.

63
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:57,600
Oh, Selena...

64
00:02:57,733 --> 00:03:00,433
Can I talk to you?

65
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,533
Okay, leave us alone for now.

66
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:11,833
Selena...

67
00:03:13,267 --> 00:03:16,067
Sorry.

68
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:19,367
Sorry for everything I've done.

69
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:23,833
You're right.

70
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:26,667
I'm stupid.

71
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,833
I'm stupid when it comes
to feelings.

72
00:03:29,967 --> 00:03:32,733
I'm also stupid when it comes
to relationships.

73
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,533
Because...

74
00:03:36,667 --> 00:03:38,400
the truth is...

75
00:03:43,267 --> 00:03:46,433
It's my first time.

76
00:03:47,967 --> 00:03:49,433
What?

77
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:51,200
What first time?

78
00:03:52,967 --> 00:03:55,700
That was my first kiss earlier.

79
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,567
So...

80
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:05,133
I'm sorry for everything
I've done.

81
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:08,433
If I ever insulted you...

82
00:04:08,567 --> 00:04:11,200
or used you,

83
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:13,900
I'm really sorry.

84
00:04:14,033 --> 00:04:17,433
But if you were already
pissed off with me earlier,

85
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:19,433
why did you do that?

86
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,433
You know...

87
00:04:24,567 --> 00:04:27,200
maybe you're just really stupid.

88
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:46,467
What are you talking about?

89
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,600
If you're mad at me...

90
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:50,833
for telling you this,

91
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:54,133
I'll understand
if you ignore me.

92
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:56,200
I can't do that to you.

93
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:03,233
Because Vince, the truth is,

94
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:06,833
I talked to Allan
to make you jealous.

95
00:05:09,667 --> 00:05:10,633
What?

96
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:14,367
What do you mean?

97
00:05:16,067 --> 00:05:17,567
Because it's your fault!

98
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:21,367
You're not doing
anything at all.

99
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:24,133
You're just staring,
you're just being cute,

100
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,500
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

101
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:31,133
So what, what...

102
00:05:31,267 --> 00:05:33,200
What Allan is doing,

103
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:35,667
what's that? Is it like a prank,
something like that?

104
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,300
Like...

105
00:05:37,433 --> 00:05:39,967
just a joke?

106
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,300
Isn't it obvious?

107
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:42,600
What?

108
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:44,800
Vince...

109
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:47,433
I like you too.

110
00:05:47,567 --> 00:05:50,467
But you, you're so shy.

111
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,867
Sorry.

112
00:05:55,233 --> 00:05:56,700
Wait a minute.

113
00:05:59,900 --> 00:06:01,333
Yes!

114
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:09,867
Does that mean you like me too?

115
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:14,067
So, with Allan trying
to court you, that's nothing?

116
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:19,000
So what now, Vince?
Are we okay now?

117
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:20,833
Yes, Bro, we're okay!

118
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,167
Sorry if I hit you.

119
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:24,867
That's nothing.

120
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,267
But, Faye...

121
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:31,833
is it okay, before you go
see your driver,

122
00:06:31,967 --> 00:06:34,367
Let me tell you something first.

123
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,833
What's that?

124
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:39,767
Can I court you?

125
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,667
Okay.

126
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:52,833
Okay, Vince,
we'll go ahead, okay?

127
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,967
Let's go.

128
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,733
Be careful.

129
00:07:07,067 --> 00:07:08,533
What, Vince?

130
00:07:08,667 --> 00:07:10,033
Are we okay?

131
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:11,067
You're so slow.

132
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:12,467
Of course, we're okay!

133
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,433
We're okay?

134
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:14,900
We had to make you jealous
first.

135
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,067
Conde, Dizon, Noble?

136
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,867
What's the update
on your interviews?

137
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:29,367
Nothing, Sir, negative.

138
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,900
But what the customers and staff
are saying is legit.

139
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:35,800
Sir, we've got all their contact
info and addresses.

140
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:37,767
Just in case,
they're easy to reach.

141
00:07:37,900 --> 00:07:39,067
As for me, Chief,
I didn't get anything

142
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:40,833
from the people
I talked to either.

143
00:07:40,967 --> 00:07:44,800
It looks like the killer got out
before the body was found.

144
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,300
And, Sir...

145
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:58,833
two gay men in a row
were killed with an icepick.

146
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:00,033
What's that, Bok?

147
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,833
Serial killer?

148
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,833
Possible.

149
00:08:04,967 --> 00:08:07,000
Nothing must come out
in the media for now.

150
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:10,367
Nothing must come out
in the media for now.

151
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,133
- Yes, Sir.
- Okay, Sir.

152
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:13,233
Okay.

153
00:08:13,367 --> 00:08:15,133
Bok, I'll go there first.

154
00:08:30,633 --> 00:08:32,600
Noble, come with me.
Let's go.

155
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:34,267
Yes, Sir.

156
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:41,833
Lord...

157
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:46,967
I know what I'm doing is wrong,
what I'm doing is cheating.

158
00:08:48,633 --> 00:08:49,733
Promise, Lord...

159
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:53,400
I really promise
that I will change.

160
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:59,933
Just remove this curse
you gave me.

161
00:09:00,067 --> 00:09:02,333
Lord, I can't do it anymore.

162
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:03,567
I can't do it anymore, Lord.

163
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:06,633
I don't want these powers.

164
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:11,667
I don't want to see anything
that has to do with killing.

165
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:17,033
Please, Lord.

166
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:40,800
Sir, what's happening?

167
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,500
Noble...

168
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:44,767
I have a strong hunch...

169
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,833
that the killer is here outside.

170
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:49,433
How can you say, Sir?

171
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:51,333
Someone tipped me off.

172
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:53,133
Who did you get
the tip from, Sir?

173
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:55,133
Is that a reliable source?

174
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:02,500
Well, just observe
everything, okay?

175
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:05,167
If you sense anything unusual,

176
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,900
ring me immediately.

177
00:10:07,033 --> 00:10:09,467
Copy, Sir.
I'll be stationed here.

178
00:10:27,067 --> 00:10:29,700
What is Tonyo
doing here outside?

179
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,933
Hey! Hey!

180
00:11:10,067 --> 00:11:11,433
Stop!

181
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,733
- Follow him, I'll go around!
- Yes, Sir.

182
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:58,333
Stop!

183
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,800
- Bobby!
- Noble...

184
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:09,433
What happened?

185
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:10,933
Noble, where's the guy
we're chasing?

186
00:12:11,067 --> 00:12:12,867
Sir, he got away.

187
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,200
What? How did he get away?

188
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:17,333
Ma'am Bobby and I bumped
into each other.

189
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:36,200
Glen?

190
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:41,767
What are you doing here?

191
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:44,000
Well, if you were replying
to my texts,

192
00:12:44,133 --> 00:12:45,833
I wouldn't be here.

193
00:12:45,967 --> 00:12:48,800
Well, I told you earlier,
didn't I?

194
00:12:48,967 --> 00:12:51,800
Yeah, billiards, you said.

195
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:53,800
Well, you didn't reply
to me when I asked

196
00:12:53,933 --> 00:12:57,400
if that annoying policeman
was with you.

197
00:12:57,533 --> 00:13:00,133
Yes, he's with me.

198
00:13:00,267 --> 00:13:02,567
But I told you a long time ago,
didn't I?

199
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:05,400
That's nothing.

200
00:13:05,533 --> 00:13:08,300
Actually, in fact,
he's dating someone else.

201
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:13,033
Well, that's good for him.

202
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:15,933
He doesn't need
to be hurt anymore.

203
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:19,700
Anyway, are you
coming home with me?

204
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:20,900
I'd love to,

205
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:24,033
but I have a lot to take care
of tomorrow morning.

206
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,800
Oh, well, are you hungry?

207
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:27,467
Because I'm hungry, let's go.

208
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:32,067
Actually, I wanted to talk
to you about my late father.

209
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,967
What about it, Glen?

210
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:38,033
I can't get it out of my mind.

211
00:13:38,167 --> 00:13:40,067
You know, when I...

212
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:43,367
I asked you to help me
with the situation.

213
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:47,933
<i> If the doctors can revive him,</i>

214
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:50,200
<i> Cecilia, listen to me.</i>

215
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:51,900
<i> I need you to...</i>

216
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:52,933
<i> do something for me.</i>

217
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:55,467
<i>Are you seriously
asking me this?</i>

218
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:59,267
<i> If my dad lives, I'm dead!</i>

219
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:01,633
<i> So please do this for me!</i>

220
00:14:01,767 --> 00:14:05,033
Are you seriously getting mad
at me for that?

221
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:06,633
Have you forgotten, Glen?

222
00:14:06,767 --> 00:14:08,633
We have an agreement, right?

223
00:14:08,767 --> 00:14:12,567
I said I'll do anything
to help you with your plans,

224
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:16,100
as long as my conscience allows.

225
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:19,933
But my conscience
has limits, Glen.

226
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,900
I know, I know.

227
00:14:22,033 --> 00:14:24,667
You're so clear.

228
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:28,833
I guess I was just thinking...

229
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:33,233
that next time you don't do
what I tell you...

230
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,533
you'd better think twice.

231
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,033
Is that clear?

232
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:16,133
Noble, sorry again.

233
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:17,467
It's okay, Ma'am.

234
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:20,200
It's nothing serious.

235
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:22,500
But Ma'am, why did you join
the chase?

236
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:24,900
I thought you already went home?

237
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:36,833
Noble, what happened there?

238
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:44,467
Sir, I had a hunch that
the killer might be out there,

239
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,633
so Noble and I went
looking for him.

240
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:49,367
Suddenly a bystander ran away,

241
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,733
so we chased him.

242
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,300
Where? Did you catch him?

243
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,567
No, Sir.

244
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:58,833
What?

245
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:02,533
There were two of you,
and yet he escaped?

246
00:16:02,667 --> 00:16:06,133
Robles, make sure you get
the identity of that bystander.

247
00:16:06,267 --> 00:16:07,800
Yes, Sir.

248
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:11,833
Submit a report tomorrow!

249
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:23,700
Oh my.

250
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,500
Oh, here, I bought bread.

251
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:27,267
Eat first.

252
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,367
Okay, breakfast.

253
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,900
Oh, there, coffee.

254
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:31,433
Captain....

255
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,867
Do you know?

256
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,100
It's been a while
since we've seen

257
00:16:36,233 --> 00:16:38,433
our friend Tootsie.

258
00:16:39,933 --> 00:16:41,933
Well, we're always busy.

259
00:16:43,033 --> 00:16:45,267
And then now...

260
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,300
she's gone.

261
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:49,267
That's right, Captain.

262
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,767
You know...

263
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:53,700
we were so close.

264
00:16:54,833 --> 00:16:57,033
It just happened that...

265
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,133
we're so busy.

266
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:01,067
That's why we didn't see each
other anymore.

267
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:04,967
What? Is that so?

268
00:17:05,100 --> 00:17:07,900
Oh my, you don't seem to feel
like eating.

269
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:10,333
-Okay, I'll just take this away.
- Oh, no, no, Captain.

270
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:13,133
- Captain, you're so judgmental.
- That's right.

271
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:14,467
Oh, your acting!

272
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,533
We were just reminiscing.

273
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,967
Good morning, Grandmother.

274
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:18,300
Oh, grandchild!

275
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:19,833
Oh, it's good you're home.

276
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:22,033
- Oh...
- Aren't you on leave?

277
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:23,300
Any news, Bobby?

278
00:17:23,433 --> 00:17:26,533
Is there a suspect
in what happened to Tootsie?

279
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,633
There is.

280
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:31,033
What? Did they catch him?

281
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:41,733
Bobby...

282
00:17:42,967 --> 00:17:44,433
what's going on?

283
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:48,600
I have to file
an incident report, Grandmother.

284
00:17:50,467 --> 00:17:52,533
Is there a problem?

285
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:58,100
Why is that, Grandmother?

286
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:00,367
I just want to help...

287
00:18:00,500 --> 00:18:02,267
but it made things worse.

288
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,267
I'll go ahead, Grandmother.

289
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,700
I'll just work in the bedroom.

290
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:27,167
So, Attorney...

291
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:29,067
I just want to know

292
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:31,233
if Joaquin's inheritance
can still be recovered

293
00:18:31,367 --> 00:18:32,833
from that illegitimate child.

294
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:35,600
Well, I could name a few.

295
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:39,033
You could make it out that
the Mayor was not of sound mind

296
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:41,967
when he made his last will.

297
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:48,633
But in that case,
there's a lot more to set up.

298
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:49,700
What else?

299
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:53,233
Let's say the documents
were forged,

300
00:18:53,367 --> 00:18:54,733
tampered with.

301
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,433
There's a problem here.

302
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:59,100
The court needs
to establish

303
00:18:59,233 --> 00:19:03,000
that the illegitimate child
had an ulterior motive.

304
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:07,133
In my experience, Madam,
that's a bit of a stretch.

305
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:09,267
Or...

306
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:14,967
we could prove that Joaquin
was coerced by that bastard.

307
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:16,800
Is that possible?

308
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:18,267
It's also possible, Madam.

309
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,933
But then again,

310
00:19:20,067 --> 00:19:23,467
that's the hardest thing
to prove in court.

311
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:27,767
Maybe it's not a good idea
to bring it up in court.

312
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:31,667
Well, Attorney...

313
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:39,200
make sure that woman
doesn't get anything.

314
00:19:40,433 --> 00:19:41,833
Do you understand?

315
00:19:41,967 --> 00:19:45,267
Yes, Madam,
I'll do it right away.

316
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:46,967
Okay.

317
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,633
Okay, Sir, we'll do
everything we can.

318
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,067
Just be careful next time.

319
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,633
Okay, Sir.

320
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:07,367
It's good that we were
able to help.

321
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,600
- Okay, Sir.
- Okay.

322
00:20:08,733 --> 00:20:10,033
- Sir, be careful.
- I'll expect that, okay?

323
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,200
Okay.

324
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,600
Mira!

325
00:20:13,733 --> 00:20:15,267
What are you doing here?

326
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,867
Don't hide it anymore.

327
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,000
I heard what happened.

328
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:19,833
Let me see.

329
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:22,133
It doesn't hurt.

330
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:23,767
It doesn't hurt?
It doesn't hurt?

331
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:26,000
Ouch!

332
00:20:26,133 --> 00:20:28,133
- Let me see.
- It doesn't hurt.

333
00:20:28,267 --> 00:20:30,300
- You...
- I was careful.

334
00:20:32,733 --> 00:20:35,567
HHWW.

335
00:20:38,867 --> 00:20:41,467
Holding hands while working.

336
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,967
Oh...

337
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,900
No.

338
00:20:46,033 --> 00:20:47,767
Just kidding.
That's okay.

339
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:52,433
As long as it's not going
to affect your jobs,

340
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:53,933
especially you.

341
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:56,333
You're named Noble.

342
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:58,433
- Stand by that.
- Of course, Sir Eric.

343
00:20:58,567 --> 00:21:00,233
We're professionals.

344
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:02,833
Yes, you can count on it.

345
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:04,600
Okay.

346
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:09,000
At ease! You may continue
your HHWW.

347
00:21:12,367 --> 00:21:13,400
- Sorry.
- It's your fault.

348
00:21:13,533 --> 00:21:15,567
Ouch! That hurts.

349
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,233
Oh, Ma'am Bobby.

350
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:21,067
Noble, how's your hand?

351
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,267
Oh, all goods, Ma'am.

352
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,000
It's not painful.

353
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:26,400
Right?

354
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:27,833
Sorry again.

355
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:30,433
Ma'am, it's okay.

356
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:33,067
I know you just want to help.

357
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:36,900
Okay, I'll go first.

358
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,500
Okay, Ma'am.

359
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:40,067
Enriquez.

360
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,867
The Chief is calling for you.

361
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:47,267
Yes, Sir.

362
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:50,933
Enriquez, come in.

363
00:21:53,067 --> 00:21:54,567
Sit down.

364
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:58,567
I've read Conde
and Noble's report.

365
00:21:58,700 --> 00:22:02,767
- Sir...
- Enriquez, I'll go first.

366
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:05,033
I'll make this as short
as possible.

367
00:22:05,167 --> 00:22:07,467
I know you have good intentions.

368
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:09,267
Why are you so stubborn?

369
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,967
Didn't I send you home
last night?

370
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:13,233
Why didn't you come home?

371
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:17,133
To make matters worse,
your partner got injured.

372
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:19,333
And because of you
and the killer escaped us.

373
00:22:19,467 --> 00:22:21,533
Sorry, Sir.

374
00:22:21,667 --> 00:22:24,600
I know you were
just worried about me.

375
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:27,500
But, Chief,
I'm really okay.

376
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:31,167
Listen, Enriquez.

377
00:22:33,267 --> 00:22:35,400
You don't have any
fieldwork for now.

378
00:22:35,533 --> 00:22:39,667
You'll have a desk job
until further notice.

379
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,700
Chief...

380
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:45,200
I understand
where you're coming from.

381
00:22:45,333 --> 00:22:48,200
Sorry for all my stubbornness,

382
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:52,000
but we have so many unsolved
cases, Chief.

383
00:22:52,167 --> 00:22:55,400
I don't think it's right
to just put me behind the desk.

384
00:22:55,533 --> 00:22:57,033
You're right!

385
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:59,767
That's why I asked
for additional support

386
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:01,633
at the other station.

387
00:23:01,767 --> 00:23:03,600
Additional support?

388
00:23:03,733 --> 00:23:05,367
She's already here.

389
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,367
Don't say it's your boyfriend
who's hurting you.

390
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:25,533
This is mom's doing.

391
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:26,567
Mom Zondra?

392
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:28,000
- He's hurting you?
- Oh my.

393
00:23:28,133 --> 00:23:29,867
- Who are you?
- I'm Tootsie's wife.

394
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,933
I'm his partner!

395
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:33,567
You're just a mistress!

396
00:23:37,933 --> 00:23:40,000
Can I interview you,
even just for a short while?

397
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:41,700
Can we find some other time
to do this?

398
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:44,367
This is about your road project
in Sitio Manggahan, Mayor.

399
00:23:44,633 --> 00:23:47,000
Do you get triggered
whenever you're touched?

400
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:50,033
When I touch a random object,

401
00:23:50,167 --> 00:23:52,467
sometimes it feels like
I'm daydreaming.

402
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:55,333
Lieutenant Paloma and I
are assigned here for now.

403
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:58,500
That means there's a case to be
solved at Station 12.

404
00:23:58,633 --> 00:24:00,100
I like your confidence.

405
00:24:00,233 --> 00:24:01,233
How's that, Bobby?

406
00:24:01,367 --> 00:24:03,133
It seems like we'll be seeing
each other a lot.
